          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Samples were irradiated with and without cadmium",
                " shield. Because 59Co and 197Au have different sensi-",
                " tivities to thermal and epithermal neutrons, monitor",
                " wires allow to determine the thermal and epithermal",
                " fractions of neutron flux"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Monitor samples are cobalt/aluminium and gold/",
                " aluminium wires which were used to monitor neutron",
                " flux at the target positions",
                "-Co/Al alloy(Co 0.46wt%, 0,381 mm in diameter),",
                " Au/Al alloy (Au-0.112wt%,0,510 mm diam)",
                ".Ho-166-m is generated from the stable monoisotope",
                " Ho-165 by irradiation in reactor. Four samples were",
                " prepared. Thickness of each is 0.0125 mm, purity",
                " is 99.9%, weighs 0.0944, 0.1203, 0.1165, 0.1030 mg.",
                " 1st irradiation of the foils was performed at the long",
                " irradiation plug of (KURRI) for 2 and 3 weeks.",
                " The second irradiation of the target was performed in",
                " a hydraulic transfer tube of Kyoto University reactor",
                " for 10 hours with and without  cadmium capsule."
              ]
            }
          ],
